    <h1> what is html tag - mdn</h1>
    <p>
        <!-- <html> -->
        : The HTML Document / Root element
        The
        <!-- <html> -->
        HTML element represents the root (top-level element) of an HTML document, so it is also referred to as the root
        element. All other elements must be descendants of this element. There can be only one
        <!-- <html>  -->
        element in a document.
    </p>
    <h1>html tag - chatgpt</h1>
    <p>
        <!-- <html>  -->
        tag HTML document ka root element hai aur saari HTML content iske andar hoti hai. Yeh tag browser ko batata hai
        ke document ka start aur end kahan hai. Chaliye,
        <!-- <html> -->
        tag ke kuch key aspects ko detail mein dekhte hain:
    </p>
    <p>Structure of
        <!-- <html>  -->
        Tag
        HTML document ka basic structure kuch is tarah hota hai:

        <!-- html
        Copy code
        <!DOCTYPE html>
        <html lang="en">
        <head>
            <meta charset="UTF-8">
            <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
            <title>Document</title>
        </head>
        <body>
            <h1>Hello, World!</h1>
            <p>This is a paragraph.</p>
        </body>
        </html>
        Is example mein, <html> tag ne saari document ko wrap kiya hua hai.</p> -->
        <!-- <h1>attributes of html  tag </h1> -->
        <h1>Attributes of html Tag</h1>
        lang Attribute:

        lang attribute document ki primary language ko specify karta hai.
        Example:
        <!-- <html lang="en"> (English), <html lang="ur"> (Urdu). -->
        Global Attributes:

        class, id, style, title, etc. are global attributes that can be used with most HTML elements, including hmtl
        tag.
        <!-- <html>. -->
        Example:
        <!-- <html id="main-html" class="container">.</p>  -->
         <h1>html tag attributes- chatgpt</h1>
         <!-- <p>Attributes of <html> Tag
            lang Attribute:
            
            lang ka matlab language hai. Yeh attribute document ki language set karta hai.
            Example:
            html
            Copy code
            <html lang="en">  English language -->
          <!--   <html lang="ur"> Urdu language -->
           <!-- Global Attributes:
            
            class:
            
            Class attribute elements ko style karne ke liye ya unko group karne ke liye use hota hai.
            Example:
            html
            Copy code
            <html class="my-html-class">
            id:
            
            ID attribute ek unique identifier hota hai jo kisi bhi HTML element ko identify karne ke liye use hota hai.
            Example:
            html
            Copy code
            <html id="main-html">
            style:
            
            Style attribute inline CSS ko apply karne ke liye use hota hai.
            Example:
            html
            Copy code
            <html style="background-color: lightblue;">
            title:
            
            Title attribute additional information provide karne ke liye use hota hai jo hover karne par show hoti hai.
            Example:
            html
            Copy code
            <html title="This is the main HTML element">
            Example Using Attributes
            html
            Copy code
            <!DOCTYPE html>
            <html lang="en" class="container" id="main-html" style="background-color: lightblue;" title="This is the root element">
            <head>
                <meta charset="UTF-8">
                <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
                <title>Example</title>
            </head>
            <body>
                <h1>Hello, World!</h1>
            </body>
            </html>
            Is example mein:
            
            lang="en": Document ki language English set karta hai.
            class="container": HTML element ko "container" class assign karta hai.
            id="main-html": HTML element ko ek unique ID "main-html" deta hai.
            style="background-color: lightblue;": HTML element ka background color light blue set karta hai.
            title="This is the root element": Additional information provide karta hai jo hover karne par show hoti hai.
            Yeh sab attributes HTML element ko specific functionalities aur styling dene ke liye use hote hain. Agar aapko kisi specific attribute ke bare mein aur detail chahiye, to zaroor batayein!
            
            
