            <html> tag mein commonly use hone wale attributes ke ilawa kuch aur attributes bhi hain jo aap use kar sakte hain. Yeh saare attributes HTML document ko customize karne aur uski functionalities ko enhance karne ke liye use hote hain. Yahan kuch aur attributes hain jo aap <html> tag mein use kar sakte hain:
            
            Commonly Used Attributes
            lang:
            
            Document ki language specify karta hai.
            Example:
            html
            Copy code
            <html lang="en">
            class:
            
            CSS classes assign karta hai jo styling ke liye use hoti hain.
            Example:
            html
            Copy code
            <html class="container">
            id:
            
            Unique identifier deta hai.
            Example:
            html
            Copy code
            <html id="main-html">
            style:
            
            Inline CSS apply karta hai.
            Example:
            html
            Copy code
            <html style="background-color: lightblue;">
            title:
            
            Additional information provide karta hai jo hover karne par show hoti hai.
            Example:
            html
            Copy code
            <html title="This is the root element">
            Less Commonly Used Attributes
            dir:
            
            Text direction specify karta hai (LTR for left-to-right, RTL for right-to-left).
            Example:
            html
            Copy code
            <html dir="ltr">  Left to Right 
            <html dir="rtl">  Right to Left -->
         <!--  manifest:
            
            Offline web applications ke liye application cache manifest file specify karta hai.
            Example:
            html
            Copy code
            <html manifest="example.appcache">
            xmlns (XML namespace):
            
            Namespace specify karta hai jab aap XML documents ke saath kaam kar rahe hote hain.
            Example:
            html
            Copy code
            <html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
            Example with Additional Attributes
            html
            Copy code
            <!DOCTYPE html>
            <html lang="en" class="container" id="main-html" style="background-color: lightblue;" title="This is the root element" dir="ltr" manifest="example.appcache" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
            <head>
                <meta charset="UTF-8">
                <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
                <title>Example</title>
            </head>
            <body>
                <h1>Hello, World!</h1>
            </body>
            </html>
            Is example mein:
            
            dir="ltr": Text direction left-to-right set karta hai.
            manifest="example.appcache": Application cache manifest file specify karta hai.
            xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml": Namespace specify karta hai.
            Agar aapko kisi aur specific attribute ke bare mein detail chahiye ya kisi particular attribute ka istemal samajhna hai, to zaroor batayein!
            
            
            
            
            
            
            </p> -->
            <p>
                Is example mein:

lang="en": Document ki language English set karta hai.
class="container": HTML element ko "container" class assign karta hai.
id="main-html": HTML element ko ek unique ID "main-html" deta hai.
style="background-color: lightblue;": HTML element ka background color light blue set karta hai.
title="This is the root element": Additional information provide karta hai jo hover karne par show hoti hai.
                dir="ltr": Text direction left-to-right set karta hai.
                manifest="example.appcache": Application cache manifest file specify karta hai.
                xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml": Namespace specify karta hai.</p>

    <h1>importance of html tag</h1>
    <p>Importance of

        <!-- <html> Tag -->
        Semantic Structure:
        <!-- <html>  -->
        tag document ko ek structured format mein organize karta hai, jo browsers aur search
        engines ke liye readable hota hai.
        Validation: Properly nested
        <!-- <html>  -->
        tag aur uske andar ke elements document ko valid banate hain aur ensure karte
        hain ke woh different browsers mein sahi tarah se render ho.
        Internationalization: lang attribute use karke aap apni website ko multiple languages ke liye optimize kar sakte
        hain, jo ke user experience ko improve karta hai.
    </p>

